The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Tamluk, July 10: Class XII student Saurav Mondal was beaten unconscious this morning by the headmaster of his school because he was not in uniform. 

 Saurav, a resident of Kanchannagar in Nandigram, was hospitalised with head injuries. Samar Manna, the head of Brajamohan Tiwari High School, apologised to Sauravs father. 

 Midnapore: The secretary of the CPMs Kantapahari branch committee in West Midnapores Lalgarh was shot dead by suspected Maoists on Tuesday. Rohit Roy, 39, was returning home from a tea stall.




